<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FF99FF91EA8D12B9FCB956C1" author="Simmons, N. B. &amp; R. S. Voss" box="[480,819,225,1727]" pageId="25" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 219" refId="ref42345" refString="Simmons, N. B., and R. S. Voss. 1998. The mammals of Paracou, French Guiana: a Neotropical lowland rainforest fauna. Part 1. Bats. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 237: 1 - 219." type="journal article" year="1998">Simmons and Voss (1998)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FF99FF91E82D14FFFC7756C1" author="Lim, B. K." box="[832,1021,225,249]" pageId="25" pageNumber="25" pagination="225 - 274" refId="ref38551" refString="Lim, B. K., et al. 2005. Results of the ALCOA Foundation-Suriname expeditions. XIV. Mammals of Brownsberg Nature Park, Suriname. Annals of Carnegie Museum 74: 225 - 274." type="journal article" year="2005">Lim et al. (2005)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FF99FF91EF6414FFFD7C5723" author="Taddei, V. A. &amp; B. K. Lim" pageId="25" pageNumber="25" pagination="381 - 386" refId="ref42798" refString="Taddei, V. A., and B. K. Lim. 2010. A new species of Chiroderma (Chiroptera, Phyllostomidae) from Northeastern Brazil. Brazilian Journal of Biology, 70: 381 - 386." type="journal article" year="2010">Taddei and Lim (2010)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FF99FF91E86C151DFC625723" author="Garbino, G. S. T. &amp; C. C. de Aquino &amp; C. C. Aires" box="[769,1000,259,283]" pageId="25" pageNumber="25" pagination="254 - 257" refId="ref35615" refString="Garbino, G. S. T., C. C. de Aquino, and C. C. Aires. 2012. First record for the state of Rondonia and revised distribution map of Chiroderma trinitatum Goodwin, 1958 (Mammalia: Chiroptera: Phyllostomidae) in Brazil. Check List 8: 254 - 257." type="journal article" year="2012">Garbino et al. (2012)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FF99FF91E899151DFB325723" author="Tello, C. &amp; G. Streicker Daniel &amp; J. Gomez &amp; P. M. Velazco" box="[1012,1208,259,283]" pageId="25" pageNumber="25" pagination="191 - 197" refId="ref42940" refString="Tello, C., G. Streicker Daniel, J. Gomez, and P. M. Velazco. 2014. New records of pigmentation disorders in molossid and phyllostomid (Chiroptera) bats from Peru. Mammalia 78: 191 - 197." type="journal article" year="2014">Tello et al. (2014)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FF99FF91E9B0153BFC265705" author="Rocha, P. A. &amp; M. V. Brandao &amp; G. Garbino &amp; I. N. Cunha &amp; C. C. Aires" box="[733,940,293,317]" pageId="25" pageNumber="25" pagination="573 - 578" refId="ref41807" refString="Rocha, P. A., M. V. Brandao, G. Garbino, S. T., I. N. Cunha, and C. C. Aires. 2016. First record of Salvin's big-eyed bat Chiroderma salvini Dobson, 1878 for Brazil. Mammalia 80: 573 - 578." type="journal article" year="2016">Rocha et al. (2016)</bibRefCitation>
. Two subspecies are currently recognized: 
<emphasis id="B90EEA8AFF99FF91E8101556FB815767" box="[893,1035,328,351]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="25">C. t. gorgasi</emphasis>
(
<collectingCountry id="F36D7608FF99FF91EF711556FBFC5758" box="[1052,1142,328,352]" name="Panama" pageId="25" pageNumber="25">Panama</collectingCountry>
south to western 
<collectingCountry id="F36D7608FF99FF91E8421574FC1657BA" box="[815,924,362,386]" name="Colombia" pageId="25" pageNumber="25">Colombia</collectingCountry>
and northwestern 
<collectingCountry id="F36D7608FF99FF91EF101574FD5F579C" name="Ecuador" pageId="25" pageNumber="25">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
) and 
<emphasis id="B90EEA8AFF99FF91E84E1592FC51579C" box="[803,987,396,420]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="25">
C. t. 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D1BFF99FF91E80B1593FC51579C" authorityName="Goodwin" authorityYear="1958" box="[870,987,397,420]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Chiroderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="25" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="trinitatum">trinitatum</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
(
<collectingCountry id="F36D7608FF99FF91E89C1592FBD3579C" box="[1009,1113,396,420]" name="Trinidad and Tobago" pageId="25" pageNumber="25">Trinidad</collectingCountry>
, eastern 
<collectingCountry id="F36D7608FF99FF91E9C115B0FC9157FE" box="[684,795,430,454]" name="Colombia" pageId="25" pageNumber="25">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F36D7608FF99FF91E84715B0FC0357FE" box="[810,905,430,454]" name="Ecuador" pageId="25" pageNumber="25">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="F36D7608FF99FF91E8A615B1FB8B57FE" box="[971,1025,431,454]" name="Peru" pageId="25" pageNumber="25">Peru</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="F36D7608FF99FF91EF2E15B0FB3257FE" box="[1091,1208,430,454]" name="Venezuela" pageId="25" pageNumber="25">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
, the Guianas, 
<collectingCountry id="F36D7608FF99FF91E83B15CEFC1157D0" box="[854,923,464,488]" name="Brazil" pageId="25" pageNumber="25">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, and northern 
<collectingCountry id="F36D7608FF99FF91EF0E15CEFB3E57D0" box="[1123,1204,464,488]" name="Bolivia" pageId="25" pageNumber="25">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FF99FF91E9D915ECFCEC5432" author="Gardner, A. L." box="[692,870,498,522]" pageId="25" pageNumber="25" pagination="321 - 326" refId="ref35846" refString="Gardner, A. L. 2008 c (&quot; 2007 &quot;). Genus Chiroderma W. Peters, 1860. In A. L. Gardner (editor), Mammals of South America, vol. 1: Marsupials, xenarthrans, shrews, and bats: 321 - 326. Chicago: University of Chicago Press." type="book chapter" year="2008">Gardner, 2008c</bibRefCitation>
). Our Mayo River basin specimen exhibits the diagnostic characteristics of the nominate subspecies: small size (FA &lt;42.5 mm, GLS &lt;
<quantity id="4C829B7DFF99FF91E99C1647FCC95449" box="[753,835,601,625]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="25" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="23.0">23 mm</quantity>
); dorsal stripe arising between the shoulders and extending across the head; muzzle short and broad; furred legs; uropatagium partially furred, lack of a conspicuous fringe of hair on its trailing edge; skull lacking nasal bones; and upper inner incisors that converge along their distal third, contacting each other at the tips (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FF99FF91E98E1756FC755558" author="Simmons, N. B. &amp; R. S. Voss" box="[739,1023,840,864]" pageId="25" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 219" refId="ref42345" refString="Simmons, N. B., and R. S. Voss. 1998. The mammals of Paracou, French Guiana: a Neotropical lowland rainforest fauna. Part 1. Bats. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 237: 1 - 219." type="journal article" year="1998">Simmons and Voss, 1998</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FF99FF91EF661756FB325558" author="Gardner, A. L." box="[1035,1208,840,864]" pageId="25" pageNumber="25" pagination="321 - 326" refId="ref35846" refString="Gardner, A. L. 2008 c (&quot; 2007 &quot;). Genus Chiroderma W. Peters, 1860. In A. L. Gardner (editor), Mammals of South America, vol. 1: Marsupials, xenarthrans, shrews, and bats: 321 - 326. Chicago: University of Chicago Press." type="book chapter" year="2008">Gardner, 2008c</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B69FF99FF91E9C31774FC0D55BA" author="Garbino, G. S. T. &amp; C. C. de Aquino &amp; C. C. Aires" box="[686,903,874,898]" pageId="25" pageNumber="25" pagination="254 - 257" refId="ref35615" refString="Garbino, G. S. T., C. C. de Aquino, and C. C. Aires. 2012. First record for the state of Rondonia and revised distribution map of Chiroderma trinitatum Goodwin, 1958 (Mammalia: Chiroptera: Phyllostomidae) in Brazil. Check List 8: 254 - 257." type="journal article" year="2012">Garbino et al., 2012</bibRefCitation>
). Measurements of our specimen fall within the range reported for the species.
</paragraph>
